\insrsid7437536\charrsid13851071 you\rquote re}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
 all dressed in your finery for the procession round the parish in the morning. Then of course you went into church - special services and - special prea
chers. It always seemed to me they used to get boiling hot and I must confess that more than once I've fallen asleep in church, although I was in the choir. And the other blighters let me sleep there. 'Course it's quite a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7437536\charrsid13851071 lad\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071  trick. Oh they were great da
ys 1/2. It's funny, I'd forgotten the sermons. One of the highlights of the year. And then of course all the - the old parishioners used to come back for that day and it made a very nice reunion, seeing all the old faces and - people you hadn't seen for t
welve months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 At that time was the sermons day round about Whit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 The end of April. Usually the last Sunday in April.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 It varies from place to place doesn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 It does - yes. Although I think it's an institution peculiar to Lancashire and Yorkshire - for sermons - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Were there any other sort of procession days that you can think off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Oh, had a field day. They used to take their banner out then. Engage a brass band and march in procession to a field somewhere on the outskirt
s and then there were all sorts of games and competitions in the field and - the coffee was brewed in - beer barrels at local brewery and taken to the field then you were given a bun and you took your own mug then you could have as much coffee as you want
ed. Very good too. But that's something they don't do now - the brewers brew coffee in the beer casks then they trundle them on a lorry in the procession to the field. They used to put some of the younger children on the lorry with the barrels.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Was grace said at meal times in your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Not always. Sometimes - mainly Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 By whom would it be said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Father or mother - which - it never seemed to be a set procedure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh my giddy aunt, yes. And morning. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did you have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Very rarely. Father said he wanted us all to pray in our own way because if he prayed for us as at family prayers there was no guarantee that we were even interested. Although we might make the c
orrect responses. So his attitude was that each one should pray for themselves. Then there was at least a chance that they would be interested. Both night and morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Is there anything you can think of would be interesting since it was very important in your family as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Only as I say - the church and school was my life for a number of years. I can't think of anything else outstanding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Was your father interested in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Not over much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Do you know what his views were?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Conservative.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Do you know why he held these views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 I couldn't tell you. I'm sorry. I - I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 What about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 She was similar. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Why would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 I don't think it was because father was Conservativ
e - I think she had sufficient - character to form her own opinion - nor did father thrust his opinion down her throat. I think it was from choice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Do you remember your father voting in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 I remember him going to vote but of course we weren't allowed in the polling booths.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 But he went to vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes, and so did mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 The only election she would be eligible to vote for before 1919 would be the 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 The general election.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Do you know what party they voted for - would it be the Conservative party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 It would be - yes. I can think I can say they were almost certain.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 In some places at that time men felt that they risked losing their job or in some cases their house if they voted different
ly from their employer or landlord - do you know if your father was ever under any pressure from anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 I don't 3/8 I don't think so - no. I never heard of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Was your father a member of the Conservative party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 I don't think so. He may 
have been a member of the Conservative club for a time. But I don't - apart from that - if he had to be member of Conservative party to join the Conservative club well I suppose he would be, but apart from that I don't think he was. He didn't take an acti
ve part in politics.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 He would not work for one of the parties at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 No. Oh no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Nor your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 When your parents were not doing their work and running the house and so on how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Reading and con - conversing I think, mainly. Because there was nothing else at the time. Oh, I - occasionally father would go and have a glass of beer. I don't think I remember mother going..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did your mother have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
She didn't, no - apart from home and church. That constituted her life. She had some friends that she very, very rarely visited but it was rarely - very rarely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did she ever go out to enjoy herself apart from visiting these friends?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Not to my knowledge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 She didn't have any sister or anybody like that that she would go out with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 No. Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Would it be about half past five when your father got home form work in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Well the - the mills finished at half past five. Half past five to quarter to six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 How many evenings a week would he spend at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh, most. Even if he went out for a drink of beer he wasn't out all evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did he spend any evenings out connected with the church for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Only the time he ran black and white minstrel club for - from the school. But of course that took him out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Once a week would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh at least. I mean there - there'd be at least one or two rehearsals a week and then there would be the conce
rts. So you could safely say two nights a week at least.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 How long a period would that cover?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh now then - a number of years I think - yes. From what they tell me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did your father take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 When he was younger - yes. Football and running. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Would that be before you can remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Oh yes, yes, because he - he told us more than once that as a boy - young man - he had to hide his running pumps on top of the toilet in the backyard so that his parents wouldn't see them. And he played football as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did he have to do that in secret as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Well, I'm hot sure about football - he didn't say that, but he had to do - he had to hide his running pumps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did he attend the races ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 No, not to my knowledge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did he bet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Well, he might have had an occasional bob on the Derby or something of that sort but not as a habit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did he or your mother belong to any savings clubs - a funeral club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes, the - there was a sick and burial fu
nd at the school that they belonged to and - then they used to save at the mill as well. They had a savings club at the mill and they paid out just before the annual holiday. And they used to save in that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters - I think you've answered the already.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Well, we haven't fought, shall I say.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Was there any one that you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Curious enough I don't know that there was. Unless it was my younger - youngest sister. I felt nearer
 to her somehow than the others. I don't know why.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Who did you play with as a child - your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Brothers and sisters and friends - neighbours friends. Really my brothers and - my brothers rather than my sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 There wasn't so much of an age gap between you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Oh dear, no. The biggest age gap with the boys in between - my elder brother and myself. But after that of course - there's Edgar two years younger then Miles was about six years younger - Charles and Jim. But, so
mehow we had no trouble mixing together. Ages didn't seem to enter into it. But as I say, we had - our own friends from school and neighbours friends of varying ages right through.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did you play in rather a large group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 More often than not. Yes, I don't think there were any small - small groups or individuals shall - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Where did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh round about the house. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Actually in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 In the evenings, the children of course, brothers and sisters. But during the day of course in summer we were off to parks. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did you play in the street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 We did play - well, yes, in the back yard and in the back street and in the surrounding streets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 What about other children homes - did you go and play there? You me
ntioned some of the games you played in the house - what other games did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Well, outside there's - oh now then, those that - the seasonal games - whip and top and - piggy, as we used to call it, I don't think they call it that now. I was read
ing in the newspaper some short time ago and I think its North East - they call it shinty. And of course the usual football and various ball games. Then we had the iron hoops that we used to race with. And of course there's cricket when we could - chalk t
hree wickets on the wall and - bowl at that. Well }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7437536\charrsid13851071 there\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
 hopscotch, follow my leader - I never forget playing that on one occasion. I was a fairly good runner - I was the last. And we went along a row of houses and - this particular row of houses they had 
their door latches outside. We used to take our caps off and all bang on the latches as we passed and of course the door-flew. But by the time I got to the last one and - to the top house the man was ready and he just caught me and gave me a sound belting
.
 Then of course we had the old cowboys and Indians and - cops and robbers and all that sort of thing. And various tricks that we used to get up to. On one occasion we - we got a basin and tied some string round the base - and - tied some string round draw
i
ng pin and pushed it in centre of the window frame. No, that wasn't it. Oh, used to tie a button to that one and then swing it to and fro - it kept tapping the window. Then we'd go and sit across the road and watch what happened. And this one with the bas
i
n we put it on the window sill and took the string from the bottom of the basin to the door handle, then kick on the door and run. When they opened the door of course they pulled - pull it open as it pulled the basin off the window sill and it dropped wit
h a crash and it just sounded the window were gone. 'Course I couldn't see the funny side of it now but I could then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Well, if we did there was trouble. We weren't strictly told you mustn't get dirt
y but - if we didn't get dirty it was quite all right but if we did get dirty we were in trouble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Were you free to play with anybody you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes. Oh yes, there were no limits put on friendships. It didn't matter who they were - unless - the
re were some poor children came living not far away and - their parents were not very clean and they were troubled with body lice and head lice. We were warned not to play with them. But apart from that - no, we'd free choice to play anywhere and with who
m we wished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did you belong to any youth organisations other than the things to do with church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 No. No, I didn't. Not until I was older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 How did you spend your free time while you were still at school? You said your life at one time was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7437536\charrsid13851071 school}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071  and church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Was - well that - that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did you have any other hobbies - did you collect anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Other than - no, other than singing. And - 'course I sang in the school choir when I was a boy and - then we sang at a few musical fes
tivals and of course rehearsal for that in the evening after school, that took a little time. But I - no, I wasn't in any organisation at all. But I never seemed to have any - any difficulty in getting the time or I don't know - looking back now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did you have any hobbies like collecting anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Or gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
No, I don't think I had any hobby apart from - well it would be my teens when I started with photography. And - brass band music. And - still carried on with the singing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did you go fishing or go for walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Walks, yes. Fishing, no. May be my attitude is unusual but - to me it is not a sport. Because a fish is only following it normal life and its caught by - a trap, by stealth shall I say, in its search for food. To me it isn't a sport.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did you have a bicycle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 For a time, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did you use it much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Well, not a great deal - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Who did you go for walks with apart from your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Just friends. Friends mainly, and brothers. But friends more than anyone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 And you played football and cricket?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did you take part in any other sports?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Well, I tried boxing but my arms seemed to be too short, so I gave that up. But I could do a little at wrestling. So I was rather fond 
of wrest - well, I liked boxing but - I'm usually on the receiving end.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 When would you be doing this?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh there again - I'm sorry - that would come in my teens. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 When you were still at school did you ever go to a theatre or a concert?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Yes. But there were - they were chosen - plays. We didn't just go to any run of the - run of the mill. It was usually - something that had a good moral tone to it. And we were encouraged to go to the classical musical concerts. And we did occasionally.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 What about a cinema?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
I did go occasionally but - even then, well, I never go now, because the - the cinema leaves me with a feeling of - dissatisfaction, I don't know why. Now, I can go to a theatre and watch a play and be completely satisfied
. I go to a cinema and see a perfectly good film but some - but it leaves me still something wanting. I don't know what it is. Whether it doesn't seem real or what I don't know. But I can go to a theatre and see a play that isn't so half as so good as the
 
film yet I enjoy the play far better and I'm more satisfied than watching a film, even thought the film is better and better acted, better cast and all the rest of it. But it always leaves me with a feeling of unsatisfaction I don't know why. So I didn't 
go very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 You didn't enjoy it as a child even?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Not much. The only ones I would go would perhaps with a crowd go to see a western.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes. I think it was about shilling a week until I started working. And then I think it went to threepence for the shilling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 You were wealthy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 I was well - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did you get your shilling a week regularly from being quite a small child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Well, maybe it was - sixpence earlier but - when I come to take notice of things and what not it - got to a shilling. Fairly early.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 This was regularly was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh yes. Usually Friday evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did that shilling have to cover all your entertainment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes. And I was expected to save some of it. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 How did you spend your shilling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Well, mainly - sweets I think. As a general rule and then - I managed to save threepence most weeks. But unfortunately I seemed to get times when - 'course I still can - have a good spend. And of course that reduced it considerably.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 The threepence a week that you saved - did you put it into the bank or the Post Office?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 No, the - school savings bank. Used to take it every Monday morning. It seemed to be a regular - majority of the schoolchildren did it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Could you withdraw this money any time you wanted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Yes. Yes. I think it was put in the Post Office after. Yes, I think it was. But used to have - I can remember used to have a long bank card that we had to take to school Sunday morning
 - Monday morning. Some children only took a penny but nevertheless it mounted up in the course of twelve months.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did you have to used any of this money with your outings with the choir or the Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Only for my own benefit. Oh yes, if I wanted any - anything extra I had to use this money. Well, on -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 That had to cover all your expenses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Yes, on - on any of the family outings - if I wanted anything I was expected to provide it myself - by the way of sweets of ice creams or anything of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 And this would apply to your annual holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 That's - oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Your spending money then would come out of this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes, yes. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did anyone outside the home help your mother to look after the house or family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 No. Except during - the births. A relative would come - or a neighbour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Was your mother ever ill that you can remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Only - before she died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 I meant earlier on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 No. No, I never remember mother being ill - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Do you remember what happened when one of your younger brothers or sisters was born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Well - the only thing I can remember really is - an aunt telling me on one occasion that - I had said, we're going to have another baby. Father's brought the bed down, int
o the front room. But apart from that I'm afraid I've no recollection of - strange enough. Because of course as children we were kept clear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Would this be the aunt that would come in to look after your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 That's right - yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 She would take care of the household would she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Well, until the girls begin to grow - grow up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 When the girls were growing up did you still have a relative come in or did they manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh - yes, I think yes, because - of course they were working
 and - father used to say that all his children were very inconsiderate - they all arrived early morning - so I suppose the girls was - well, I don't know what the would do frankly. And then aunt would come in during the day as soon as she could sort of. 
I don't remember her staying. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did your parents have relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Well - what's the distance - oh well it wasn't quarter of a mile but it wasn't on the doorstep sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 How much would they see of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh I really couldn't say. Sometimes - weekly. And other times it might be months before they met. But there was no set pattern.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Was there any set pattern as to whether they would visit each others homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 No, I don't - well, my main recollect 3/8 of course
 I don't know what my parents did - whether they went up to their homes - but my recollections are of my - aunts and uncles coming to our house. And where they went from there of course I haven't the foggiest. I suppose father and mother did go to their h
ouses occasionally - well, to meet them I mean - as well as them come to us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Do you remember as children being taken to visit aunts and uncles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh yes, yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did your parents have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Well - in their younger days I suppose 
- well, they - they still kept up their friendship but they - they didn't sort of go out with them. They were all very friendly and their friends used to come and visit us and then perhaps - mother'd go and visit her friends some - perhaps during the week
.
 During the daytime or that. And - I suppose father would go and - although, as I say, at one period he had the - minstrel troupe at school and - he was in the church choir and all that sort of thing. But I don't think he had any particularly close friend
s - that he used to go and visit or they visit him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did your parents share the same friends at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Well yes, I think they did. Except for perhaps two that were mother's friends when she was a schoolgirl. Although even - well of course she didn't visit them very often. But they came to visit her. I don't ever remember them going out together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Were friends invited into the home - specifically invited to come?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Well I suppose they would be. And then of course they used to drop in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did they drop in rather than be specially invited or would it be both?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Well it was a case of both - yes. I couldn't say that it was either one or the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Would that be very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 No, I wouldn't say - occasional would be - nearer - the point than often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Would the friends be offered anything to eat or drink when they came?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh yes, yes, always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Would they be invited to come for particular celebrations - particular days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes, that did happen. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 And they would drop in casually without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 True.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Would neighbours ever he invited into the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Occasionally. It wasn't that - we remained aloof or anything. Some of the neighbours did - the next door neighbours came in of course. And mother wen
t in next door on each side as well. But I don't recollect them being invited for any particular celebration.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 If your neighbours dropped in would your mother offer them anything to eat or drink
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh yes, yes. She would ask them would they like a drink or a bite or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 People say that in those days they used to make their own amusements.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes, that's quite true.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 What do you think your parents did when they were together with their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh now then I don't - mainly singing I think. Because both father and mother were singers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Would there possibly be any other kind of musical activity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Well, I don't know about their friends. I'm afraid I'm lost there. No, I'm sorry, I - I really don't know how they spent their time.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 You don't know whether they would possibly play games of any sort or would it be more likely to be conversation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Well - there'd be conversation certainly. I don't know that there would be - possibly would be games. I know there was in th
e house with the family but I don't know about my parents - with their friends. I don't think - cards would be on the - or dominoes or anything like that, those types of games. No, I'm sorry I can't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 People divide society into different social classe
s or groups in the time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Well, I regarded the - the professional classes as a - being a cut above - in a different classes. And I regarded our family as a working class family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Do you mean by that that you would say there were two classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Well - possibly two or three from reading the newspapers. Because - my summing up, even in a - in a professional class if they had to earn their living strictly speaking they we
re working class although they may regard themselves as middles class. But I'm not saying that in a derogatory sense. But - from reading the newspapers it - to me there was the upper class, the moneyed people who didn't work at all and then the middle or 
professional class and the working class. Or should I say the working class - non-professional - tradesmen and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Which class would you say you belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 The working class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 What sort of people belonged to the same class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Belonged to 
the same class? Well I should say all - tradesmen and skilled workers - at least that's my definition of the working class - those who had to - well, the professional are more set out if it comes to that but - I've never tried to define this before. Well,
 
I should say those who had to - well it's not strictly under supervision - there would be what is known as the artisan class of course. And the clerical classes - if you can call them classes. Well, in fact, broadly speaking all - below the professions. T
hat might cover it I think. Can't just confine it to those that worked with their hands. Because even clerical workers are still in the same grade. Up to a certain - under a certain level. I don't know whether that would satisfy -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another sort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
No. No. We were taught to treat everyone alike and that was with respect. Irrespective of what - what they were. Either higher or lower or more fortunate or less fortunate. It was one standard all through.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Were you ever told to touch your cap to anybody? Make any show of respect in any way to any particular people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Well, of course, as boys we had to touch our caps to - any superior person such as teachers or -
 anyone who was considered in a better position than we were and address the men as Sir and - so forth. But not simply because of the position.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 I must say that. We were taught to treat everyone with respective irrespective of their position. And if 
I was speaking to an uncle and if I - if I met him I had to raise my hat. Otherwise if it became known I was in trouble,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Who would you have to call Sir or Madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Well, the teachers, doctors, clergymen. 'Course we do - we call the teachers Sir as
 a matter of habit in class. But anyone who we thought was in superior position. Or that we though merited it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 By virtue of the sort of person they were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 That's right. Yes. And not necessarily on account of their worldly wealth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Do you remember anybody showing respect to your parents in this sort of way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 What sort of people or who in particular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Well - people more or less like myself and - well, that's a bit unkind - well, should I say people from whom you'd expect
 - respect from. By - by that I mean such as - she happened to meet the - a person. He would show respect in the same way or - how in the world can I put it -someone who had a decent - education and upbringing, I just can't pinpoint any -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 You mean it would be a sort of mutual respect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 That they would show for each other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Yes, I think it would. Because I don't know that it was - particularly for their own special benefit. Yes, I think that would fit the bill - mutual respect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 In the area where you lived who would you say were considered the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Of course a clergyman would stand high on the list and the doctor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 And you would come into contact with both?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 As far as the clergyma
n was concerned would you say he was considered important by most people living around or just by families such as your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes. No I - yes, at the time I would say the clergyman earned his own respect in the district. This particular one anyway - b
ecause it didn't matter what denomination they were, if he heard there was sickness he was there. Whether they wanted him or not. If they didn't want him well and good. If they did want him well it's quite all right. And - yes, I can say that - that he wa
s respected all round the district.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 What about the shopkeepers - who would they associate with? Were they corner shop type of shops?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 There were corner shops.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 How did this fit into the community life of the district?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Well some - were qu
ite friendly and well respected. And others - How shall I put it - they were, not actually disregarded, but they were just tolerated in a business sense, but that's about all. But - others - in fact, I'd one particular shopkeeper in mind although he was a
n Irishman - he and his family were - oh, they were real good. And unfortunately I don't know if you saw it - his son was murdered not long ago - Paddy Kearns. His father and mother were characters. I liked Paddy as well. He was a good lad.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did they mix freely with people round about or were there specially kind or considerate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Yes, they mixed but unfortunately Mrs Kearns was rather bad on her feet and she didn't get out very much. And - of course, as it happened they were of the Roman Catholic p
ersuasion and - quite naturally I suppose they were rather more friendly with those who attended the same church but - on the whole - in the whole district they were quite - well respected and they fit in beautifully. Both hard working people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Your clergyman was well respected?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Mixed freely with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Anyone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Would you say that was common of the clergy round about at that time or was he one who was special?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 No, I do not think it was common. Of course, at that time I w
ouldn't come into contact with many. Although there were several churches round about. But from what I saw of them in - when I grew a little older - no, one was rather - getting toward old age - fussing - only spoke when spoken to. Another one didn't seem
 to bother at all. And another one - he just bothered with his own people, that's all. Yes, that would sum it up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 What sort of people would they have as their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Well I don't know about that. I should suppose - people from their own class i
f you like, or circle. Apart from the parishioners or whatever they are. I don't think many of them made friends - personal friends with the parishioners. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 You mean they would make friends with other professional classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Well yes. Yes. That 
- that's a better answer than mine. In other words I don't think they would make friends with the common people. Although they - as you say, they were in their }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9724092\charrsid13851071 pastoral}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071  care.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 What about the teachers - what sort of people did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Oh they weren't quite so hidebound. They seemed to mix - from what I could see - they seemed to mix with - mix with all sorts. Not necessarily the dregs but - anyone who could keep up a - an intelligent conversation. Regardless of class - yes. I think the
y were very broad minded in that respect - at all events.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 That seems to have varied in different areas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Maybe we were lucky in the teachers we got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Would there have been any farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 No. No, not in the area. Although strangely enough 
opposite our house was what they called the milk house and it had been a farm house in - previous years. 'Course all the farm had gone and there was just the milk house left, just like an ordinary house and they did - they were dairymen actually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Was that just a coincidence or was it a ralic of the past?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Well, I think - well it was a relic of the past I think. I never knew it as being a farm house and - it was known locally as a milk house and they both sold milk at the house and - delivered it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Was the term milk house the normal way of describing what we would now call a dairy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Yes. Yes. That was the expression. As I say, it just slipped out without any thinking. The milk house, because in a way it wasn't much else. Except as I say - 
they were what we should now call dairymen. And old Parkinson looked like a farmer too. He was a real John Bull. About five feet ten and good wide shoulders and a beautiful red face.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Would there be any employers living in that area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 I can't thin
k of any offhand. Except - those little forge - wheelrights - Dixons That was a family business and they employed about four men. I can't think of any other employers living in the district.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Most of Bolton's employers were at Chorley New Road or out of town altogether?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 That's right - on - on the cutskirts - the west end or outskirts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Suppose I ask it in relation to your father's employer for instance, or your employer when you first started work who may not have lived locally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 No, they didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did they live in town at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Father's did not. He lived in Southport. And that was in my first work - I started at the same place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 That would hardly apply then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 What sort of people would you say went to the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
In general or - well it's difficult to classify them. Because you have the - the true, really religious element - then you have the element that go simply because it's the fashion in some respects. Others who go just as a mutual benefit club and then
 others go who - well, quite frankly I wonder why they go. Because they seem to criticise everything and everyone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Would this be true in earlier years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Well, I should say - yes. But I should think the main reason that people went to church then 
was because it was the fashion. In the Vic - Victorian period and the end of Victorian period that would be - what, Edward the seventh wouldn't it, 1911. Was it not 1912 when he - oh, I think it was Edward VII in 1911. Yes I think it was the fashion to go
.
 I - maybe I'm misjudging people but I don't think there was any more real religion in people then than there is now. The difference is that - today they stay away and openly admit they couldn't care less. But then it was the thing to go. In my opinion. A
n
d if I'm digressing a little I think that's where the clergy lost their image. Due to - the large congregations they got, I do think they were tempted to sit on their laurels. And were rather complacent. And of course then the clergyman was a person remov
e
d and separated - he wasn't one of the common herd at all. And in some cases the clergyman - of course I can see all this later now - the clergyman would enter into the lives of his parishioners and quite a lot didn't. I think the only difference really -
 
we don't get the numbers in church now - because the clergy have lost their image. But I think the classes that go are relatively the same that went then. Except the numbers are smaller. And the - well, those who don't go are a little more honest. Because
 
- well, I know there were some people came to our church - simply because their employer attended. And they considered it politic to do the same. And I came across that in a number of cases. Whether they thought their job depended on it or not I don't kno
w
. But I spoke to some of them privately and they'd no time for church really. But they considered - it was in their interest to come since their boss came. And I think the - the classes that are coming now are still the same, they were the same classes th
en.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Would you say there was any difference in the sort of people who went to the Church of England churches and the free churches and the Roman Catholic church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 In what way? Well, it seemed to me - then - 'course I've learned different - differe
ntly since - that - the Church of England and the Roman Catholics were rather more broad minded than some of the free churcher. But I don't think that obtains now. I think so far as that goes the free churches are far more broad minded than they were.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
What about the social classes of people constituting the congregations of the different types of churches - would you say that they were the same or were there differences of balance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Well I think - if the truth be known - at least my observations a
re or were - that in the Church of England I think it was the - the moneyed classes that went rather than the - working classes. But in the Roman church they get all sorts. And I think in the free churches - it was more the working - shall I say - I use w
o
rking class for want of a better term - working class with a minority of all the moneyed people. At least that's how it seemed to me. Actually this conversations doing me good - it's making me think. Because these are questions I've never had fired at me 
before. And having to answer them straight off the cuff - it - yes, I think - I think that was about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Was there any friction between the different churches?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh yes. Well, from the younger end at all events. Oh we used - what was it we used to 
call the Roman Catholics - something about dirt - dirty old Catholics - of course they called us Proddy dogs. But I don't remember the free churches ever having a nickname. No, it's just the Roman Catholics and Church of England, I don't think there was a
n
y friction between the Church of England and the free churches. 'Course I can't say about the Roman church and the free churches. Oh and of course if - two or three Protestants met a Roman Catholic well, you could be sure that Roman Catholic would be beat
en. And vice versa - if two or three Roman Catholics caught a Protestant the same happened there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Would this be just amongst the young people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 No, I - I think there was - there was bigotry among the adults. On both sides - as there still is. I'm 
sorry to say. It's rather curious that at one time - one of my friends was Roman Catholic and went to - to church and school with him. And strange enough I was accepted. Whereas had I gone alone I should have been beaten up sort of thing. No, I'm sorry to
 
say there - there was bigotry on both sides. I never saw it myself but - I heard on one occasion that - Roman Catholic and Church of England people got into a scrap to such an extent that - Dean Averdog from St Edmunds came out to - with his whip and - to
 separate them. As I say, I never saw it, it's only hearsay so far as I'm concerned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 And these sort of scraps would start of without any particular provocation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh well you see -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Would it be a matter of principle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes, it were simply t
hat - it was just like oil and water. The very fact that he belonged to the Roman Church - that's it, go on. And in the same way when they met us, oh they're Protestants, right, here we go. Oh no, it didn't need any provocation at all. The very fact that 
you're a different persuasion was sufficient.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Would it be very unusual then for friendships to exist between individuals and the Catholics church and church of England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Now then - it did exist. I don't know. Apart from my own case. But I don't th
ink there would be a great many. I think one drawback was the uncompromising attitude of the Roman Church - that their members mustn't go into the church of another denomination. That it was a sin if they did. I don't think there would be a great many but
 there were some I do know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Was there ever any sort of holding down in the street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Well, only rare occasions among the adults I think when they came to blows. As I say, I never saw any adults come to blows but - among the children - oh yes, that
 was quite common. Whenever we met them, either coming home from school or going to school, anywhere, anytime. It was just election time - if you're a different colour that was sufficient provocation. It didn't matter whether you believed it or not, if yo
u
 wore a different colour and you run up against some of the others you were for it. Just the same with religion. And I don't frankly now looking back - I don't think any of us had the slightest ideas of what we were talking about and making a song about. 
But it just seemed to be the thing to do so we all carried on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
In the district where you lived would you say that all the people in the working class had the same standard of living or would there be groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh no. No they hadn't all the same sta
ndard of living. But I wouldn't say they were in groups. No some of them were in very poor circumstances.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Do you know of a particular family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Well, one family - I know four of them - had to make a meal - a mid-day meal off a ha'pennyworth of chi
ps. So they wouldn't get very far on that. And some few streets away - the single houses - well, they were in poor circumstances. In fact we were regarded as being in the better houses. There's no question - we were better off than some of them. But older
 I get the more clearly I can see it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 What sort of job would the breadwinner have in a family which was really poor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Casual labourer. No skill at all. I can only remember one family where the breadwinner was a skilled man but they were in poor ci
rcumstances and - that was because he drank practically all his money. But apart from that the - the type that - shall I say the down and cuts - were the casual labourers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Do you think that any group felt itself superior to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes. I thin
k those with the - the better jobs and the white collar workers considered themselves superior. Particularly the white collar workers. They did think they were a cut above since they apparently didn't work with their hands they weren't the working class. 
Forgetting of course it's working even if the brain.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Were some families thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes. Yes, some families were. And others were a rung higher up the ladder, or at least regarded as being a rung higher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Would this depend on the nature of the job of the father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Not necessarily. I think it would depend more on the character of the parents then just how they brought the children. It wasn't necessarily the - shall I say the poorer strata that had the roughest children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Do you remember a distinction of this kind between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes. Particularly when I got into my teens. Strong distinction.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Would they associate at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Sometimes - it all depend. But not if they could h
elp it. About the only place where they night associate would be the pub I should think. When they'd had a few drinks they might associate but - not normally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes.
 I must say that I never knew them to make fish of one and flash of another. And they taught us to be the same. Depending rather on what a man was rather than what he had.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 I think - looking back - yes, I think she saw herself, shall I say, as belonging to the upper working class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Why would that be - was it because of your father's job or the house where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Well, it really a combination of all those
 plus - her own background. Mind you, I don't know - yes - I'm merely surmising this now. When I'm looking for reasons for the attitude. Yes, I think it would be combination - of them all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 You think she would marry within her class as it were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Well, yes. Certainly not below.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Was it possible at that time to move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
It might be possible. I think they would have to leave the district - and go to another district - then it might be possible. But I don't think it would be possible if you stayed where you was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Can you remember anybody who did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Only by marriage. Oh yes, one girl - curious enough it's the family I quoted a short time ago, about them being in such poor straits - and she was fortunate - fortunate enough to - marry a man who was in line for his father's business and - they }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13387931 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071  of course, they lived in the district just after they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13387931 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071  but - moved out shortly after. And now - her daughter - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13387931 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
 - Piltington, the glass man. So that's a re
al step up. Funny thing I thought about her when I read that her daughter was marrying Pilkington - and I thought of this particular incident. Good luck to them - I don't begrudge them - they can get ahead do by all means. I don't blame anyone for getting
 ahead - I say good luck to them and all credit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes, the Vicar's wife for one. A lady. Of course the Vicar as well, he was described as a gentleman. And one of the doctor
s. And one man at church - he was mill manager. I think everyone regarded him as a gentleman. Well, he wasn't a christian.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Why would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Well, his attitude to everyone. His employees and every - he was just the same it didn't matter a butto
n who it was. He treated everyone alike and I never heard, - well, of course, I didn't work for him - but I never heard him raise his voice once. By that I mean raise it in anger or - even irritation. And - he had a wonderful habit of consoling people. I'
ve never known a man like him in that respect. And if he knew of any trouble at all he would go and do what he could and many, many a time he's just slipped them little financial help as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 His work people do you mean or anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes, anyone -
 it didn't matter. If he knew them or he got to know of them he would go. He was a wonderful man. And he'd several curious sayings and one was - there's always a way done when there is no way. Another one was - it's far better to put the flowers on your m
other's bonnet rather than on her grave. And he was - well, won't say constantly - but he seemed to have a saying for - every particular occasion - just fit the bill. He was a wonderful man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Do you remember seeing a policeman around when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Oh yes, yes. The old fashioned policeman. Noted more fro brawn than brain. But nevertheless they - they did a good job - and I think they certainly - kept the younger end under better control than the present police. 'Course the present police ha
ven't the authority.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 What did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Well my feelings were mixed. We had to keep out of his way but - he was all rights if you wanted - if you were in trouble. But as far as possible keep out of his way. 'Course we were brought up to have a healthy respect for law and order.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Were you ever told if you were naughty that your parents would call a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh, I suppose - I suppose I was but - I was never scared of him in that respect. No, I was - to mind I was chary of them 
unless you're in trouble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 How do you think they treated people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Well, I think then there was far more human understanding from the police, then there is now. Maybe - the speed of life was much slowere and they - they'd time to do it. Mind you, I
 do not envy the police today. They've a most unenviable task. And I think the police then were more human because I think it's impossible for a policeman to be human today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Do you think they were allowed more discretion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes. I'm sure they were
. Yes. Because - I know several cases where the policemans caought - lads doing things and instead of taking them down to the policestation they've given them a good hiding. And that's been sufficient. Well in fact I can remember one man now and he got a 
-
 a name for himself. P.C. Edwards - I don't think he could have run the length of this room - eeh, he had a beautiful bay window - and - I remember him - seeing him catch some lads - they just took - of course they wore a short cape then - he just took hi
s
 cape off and swung it round and caught these two lads. They were down on the ground almost out. And he - he got a reputation for it - his whipping that cape round. 'Til the lads always fought shy - they knew - he - he was anywhere about they were off. Th
e
y had a healthy respect for the law that is missing today. And I think it was simply through the personal relations. If a policeman caught a boy doing some-thing instead of bothering down there and going to the juvenile court and whatnot - a good hiding -
 
and I think it did far more good - in most cases. Of course, if he happened to come across a persistent offender well, there was only one answer. But in the main - one hiding was sufficient. It taught a far better lesson than going to court. And when they
 
did get out of the court, oh, they were ostracized, they were beyond the pale - their families would all know. Or at least the lads of that family. They weren't regarded as heroes as they are nowadays. Oh no, it was regarded a blot on the escutcheon - to 
go down to the police court.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 This would be the view of the people of the same age group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 It wouldn't be imposed upon them from their parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh dear me, no, no. Oh well, of course they come against it just as I did. Perh
aps I was more fortunate that I was never caught doing - oh, I beg your pardon - once in the afternoon after school - I'd be about six or seven lads - and - we were having a walk and we went up Dean Clough - and - somehow we got on the Deane Golf club - o
n
 the golf links. And we were larking about as lads do - we weren't doing any damage or anything - I will say that - we didn't damage anything - we were just simply on the fairway. Anyway someone spotted us and - we were all roped in. We had to go before t
h
e committee and - make a public apology - otherwise it was the police. 'Course we all duly went and made the - our apology. And there the matter dropped. Well that was about the only time that I fell foul of the law. And anyway it was a private law - it w
asn't the police. Oh no, it didn't stem from their parents - it - it was the youngsters own attitude. Plus the - the attitude of the police.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 No. Well, it was our own really but it was - on a mortgage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Do you remember ever feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Not as a boy. It was only when I grew older that I realised they must have made some sacrifices for us. But not when I was younger. Because as I say we - there was always sufficient foo
d and clothing and - warmth and bedding and a few coppers for pocket money. It's only when I got older that I realised - that they must have made some sacrifices when we were - when we were young. Then of course by the time I began to work well, there wer
e one or two bringing money in that cased the situation considerably.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Do you remember any occasion when your father was ill or any occasion when the budget would be reduced because of sickness or short time or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 He was never on 
short time but I remember him being ill on one occasion. He - had an accident at work - in the room above the one he happened to be in there was a carboy of - what I said was it - anyway it doesn't matter. It was a carboy of acid got overturned and it dri
p
ped through the floor onto father's head. 'Course he'd no head covering and - that set up irresiplus. And I remember him being at home with that but I couldn't say now whether - I don't think - his wage was stopped for that. I don't remember circumstances
 being straitened because of that. It may have been, I don't know, I think I was rather too young to know. That's about the only time I remember him being at home - remember him being sick at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 But you think there was a possibility that his wage would continue?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 That's right - yes. Oh yes, I think there were strong possibility.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 You mean because this was an accident at work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Well, of course, I don't know just what - although I never remember him missing his wage. No, not even for holid
ays. No, whether on this occasion it was as a result of the accident or not I never remember him missing his wage. I can't say he didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Pay for sickness and holidays would be rather unusual at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Except for certain members of the staff.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Was he in what would today be regarded a salaried position?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes, yes. On the staff sort of thing. He would pay - would be paid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Where other people wouldn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 That's right. Yes, it's what they used to call on the staff. And they were 
paid work or play - wasn't no matter what happened. As I say, I never knew him to lose his pay at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did you get any help from the guardians or the parish or any charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 No. None.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 The next sections on your school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh that - there won't be much there I don't think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Were you given your lessons by one of your parents, a tutor, or governess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Neither - I went to school. Oh, I suppose mother - did a little before I went to school. I don't know what age I was when I went - wheth
er it was three or five. That's right. Yes, I think it was - I can't say now whether it was three. I seemed to go very early.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did you go all day when you first started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes. Up to - the age of twelve. Then I went - became what they call half-time. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 What were the school hours?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
I think - oh, I can't just remember about the younger ones - but I think it was nine to twelve and two 'til half past four. Particularly about that time - 1911.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 When you first started at three if you were three would you go for a shorter time than that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Oh yes, I don't think we were there so long. I'm trying to think whether we went at nine o'clock or not. Possibly not. Then I think we were finished about three. We weren't there long in an afternoon
, I remember we - we finished before the - the other school, the bigger school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 What kind of school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Church of England primary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Which would be a day school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Was it mixed - boys and girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 How did you get to school and how long did it take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh, about two or three minutes. Were quite close.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did anybody go with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 I fancy my elder brothers - or sisters would me take me for beginning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did you go home for your mid-day meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
I didn't like it at first. And it was only - when I got older that I could see any benefit in it. It was like purgatory for me for a beginning. And then, as I say, as I got older I - I got on more subjects I began to see a little meaning in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 What was it about it that you didn't like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
I think originally it was the fact that I was no longer free. And - I had certain things to do while I was at school. Restrictions I should say that were placed on ones liberty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Some I liked and some I didn't - it all depended on the personality of the teacher. On the whole I got on with them fairly well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did they emphasise certain things as being important in life - things like manners and tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Oh yes. And - I can see one or two now - being hauled up to the head's office for dirty shoes or clogs. And of course as boys will we were wrestling and whatnot in the schoolyard before we went in t
hen we had to show our hands and of courses they were black. So we got the cane. Then we had to go and wash them. And - of course the school doctor came periodically and - all had to be examined then if there were - there were some children with head lice
 
- well, the teacher gave them a note take to their parents. To - to get it altered - which was fair enough. Yes, I think - frankly, I think the teachers did a better job then than they do now. 'Course it may be that they had the authority then where they 
haven't now. They can't enforce any orders.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Were they particular about your being punctual?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes. That was another aspect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 What about way of speaking? Did they bother about that or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Not on the whole. No. No, they were mainly concerned with the three R's. Plus decent living and cleanliness of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 If you did something that the teacher disapproved of what would happen - you mentioned the cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Well - that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Were there any other sorts of punishment that they would inflict?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Not often. We had to - stay in after school and - usually had some - well, we - we call 'am mathematics now - but they were sums then. And particularly - I must admit at that time I wasn't good on arithmetic at all - so a double punishment to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did you ever have any punishment like standing in the corner and this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 No. The only punishments I remember were - the cane and this sort of imposition.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Were girls punished in the same way as boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes. But not
 with the same severity so far as the cane is concerned. Except until we got into the higher forms when the teacher didn't use the cane - he got the boys by the short hair and lifted them out of their seat. But - the girls more or less get - they got the 
imposition, that - they got no physical punishment. But they did in the early classes. But - the - of course not to the same extent as the boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did they ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Yes - and - what have you learned? Then of course we began to get bits of homework and - they were most interested in that. And if ever they saw the teachers - of course they didn't have the reports as they do now - the - periodical reports after
 each term - and if ever they saw the teachers of course - they wanted to know how we were going on, in fact, most of the teachers passed our house going home from school so mother used to wait at the gate and waylay the teacher and - she got her report o
n the lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Were there ever any opportunities for your parents to visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Not in the school hours. Unless they came to make a complaint or something. I - I don't just mean my parents - any parents. But there were never any - open days or - parent-teacher meeting anything of that sort as there is nowadays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did the other children attending the school come from similar types of home to yours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes. Well, more varied, probably. Oh yes, there were all sorts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Would the majority be from homes like yours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Yes, I think they would. Or poorer homes in some cases - in quite a great many. Laybe because it was - the only church school in the district I don't know. That may have been the reason but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the rest?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Some teachers - not all. Once or twice if they get a bright pupil they would - play with him a little, by that I mean help them. But on the whole there was very little of that done. Then of course
 there were - there were the usual scholarships to what we called higher grade schools then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Not particularly. Well - there might be a gang in the sense that certain ones just got together at school.
 And if they lived near each other they were together after - after school. But apart from that there were - no organised gangs or anything of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Were there any children who seemed to be left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 If they had some defect at all - some physical defect - almost certainly. Or if they couldn\rquote 
t sort of - run with all the rest, well they just wouldn't bother with them - they - they sort of went to the wall. Case of a weaker one dropping out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did you go on to another school after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 No. Only for evening school. Or night classes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 You left at twelve?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 No, no, thirteen actually when I finished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 You became a half-timer at twelve?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Half timer at twelve and left at thirteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 If you could have stayed longer would you have done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
I don't think so at that time - because - I'd heard such wonderful stories of what it was like working all day and what a grand time they had. But I can see now that if I had my chance to come over again - I most certainly would have st
ayed. But I didn't get wisdom until it was too late. In that direction.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 What sort of evening classes did you attend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Well it was just a furtherance of the day school that I'd left. Was similar subjects. General education - yes. If you want to pu
t it that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 It wasn't a vocational subject?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh no, no. No. Just - no, just general education.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Were those evening classes at the higher grade school or somewhere like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 How long did you go on doing that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 About - three - three to four years, I couldn't just say definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Can you remember what sort of subjects you did - was it the whole range of the school curriculum? Did you do anything new?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 No I - I don't think we did. But if I remember rightly I don'
t think we - bothered about reading or English or grammar. 'Cos I cut a lot out didn't I? No, we certainly did not take reading and I don't think we took either English or grammar at the night classes. But otherwise it was just as at day school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 How many evenings did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Two. Sometimes three. Tuesday and Thursday and sometimes Tuesday, Thursday and Friday.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Was this extra evening something special laid on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 No. No, it was part of the pattern. I think it usually run from seven to nin
e. Just two hours. But somehow - there didn't seem the same authority at the night classes as there were was in the day classes, I don't know why. Was the same - not the same - our teachers - but - they were day school teachers. Somehow there was differen
ce.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Different atmosphere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Oh entirely - yes. Whether they thought they couldn't treat us the same way or not I don't know they - the authority was there and the discipline was there, but somehow there was a different atmosphere entirely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Would these be quite voluntary attendances?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes. Oh yes. Quite voluntary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Which would possibly account for there being a different atmosphere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 No, I don't think that aspect altered it. I don't quite know the reason for the difference. Althoug
h I admit I never tried to analyse it until now. Difficult to remember now just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 You think the difference would be instigated more from the teachers angle than from the pupils angle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Well, I think so, yes yes. I think it would stem from the teacher. Had some good teachers too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Do you feel you benefited from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh most certainly. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Do you think you benefited from your ordinary day school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes. Yes, they gave me the grounding. And from that of course I was able to build
. And then - I gained more from night classes and I think as time has gone on I've built further and further still. Because it became entirely voluntary then with little or no supervision.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Do you think you got the benefit from school during the year you were a half timer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Was that educationally wasted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Wasted in my opinion. And I missed on - two or three activities that - the whole timers got, for instance, they went to what we call the Technical school one day a week. That was for
 - well, we were taught how to use - tools and woodworking and - a little - mechanical work - how to used different tools. I mean, that was just one, but I think I would have been better if I could have had - because I was only getting half of what the ot
h
ers were getting during the day. And I would say that was wasted - that last year. I think it would have been better rather to have cut it off at twelve and started evening classes rather than - go the half day as I did. But of course that was the custom.
 I'd no say in the matter and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Do you have any regrets about your education looking back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
My regret is that I didn't get enough. And of course if I had me time to come over again I would certainly get far more. But I do give credit to the - the 
teachers that - took me among others. Because I got a through grounding. And I think that stood me in good stead since. Because no matter what sort of structure or edifice it is, if you've no foundation you cannot build. And whislt we may not have got a l
o
t or nor did we tackle as many subjects as they do today, still the subjects we did tackle we got a thorough grounding. And after all that was the object of going to school then at that age. But my big regret is that I couldn't have gone on. But anyhow I'
ve managed to use some opportunities since.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 While you were at school did you have a part time job or any means of earning a little regular money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Until you came on to this half time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 No. I didn't - no. No, one of my brothers - did deliver newspapers. He wanted some extra pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Your first job would be as a half timer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 What was this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 It's a little difficult to describe. What they call a card lacer, in weaving mill and the design for the 
looms is punched into a series of cards and the cards were laced together with string and then they're all put on a frame up - high up above the - loom and they're all fastened together and as they come round they come flush with a great bank of punches, 
s
ort of thing, metal punches, and they go through the holes and that lets certain - reels or yard down onto the cotton as it's coming through the loom and they make the pattern that way. And my job was lacing these cards together at each end - they were pe
rforated at each end - and making sort of endless blts of them. Not a skilled job by any means.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 How did you get this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Well I fancy father saw they wanted one and - thought I was in line for earning for some money so - it wasn't much, it was t
he princely sum of half a crown a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 What hours did you work - did you work the normal mill hours for the half day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes, oh yes. Six o'clock 'til twelve and - one week you worked in morning and then the week you worked afternoons it was one '
til half past five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 What about Saturdays and Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
When you - worked the morning you finished at Friday dinner. When you worked the afternoons you worked Saturday morning. To even the hours out. Because you was extra hours with the two hours 
each morning - six to eight. And - it was six to eight then - half past eight to half past twelve then in the afternoon one 'til half past four and Saturday morning six 'til twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did you have any holidays while you were working as a half timer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Let me see - yes I think - the mill had a week in June. Yes. And - two days in September. But of course in the school holidays during that twelve months - when I wasn't - the half day I wasn't working at - of course I was free then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Were you padi at all for the holidays you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 No, oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Your half crown a week - did you feel it was a fair wage or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Well I don't - I'm afraid I didn't consider that at the time. No, I - can - thinking back now, I don't think it was particularly go
od. Because - when I went full time for the great sum of five bob a week, I hadn't been doing it a great long time when - some of my friends worked in the spinning mill and they told me what a great time they had and they got nine shilling a week. So I le
ft that and went into the spinning mill. For nine shillings a week as against five.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did you give any of the half crown to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh give it all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 What was it spent on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh I think - just general - I couldn't say what -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did you get any of it back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Well, as I told you before, I got a shilling so that must have been out of the half crown. When I started working. And then - then as I got older and earned more - my pocket dropped a penny in the shilling although actually it w
as more in amount. But in ratio it was less than I got when I was younger. Actually I got more when I was younger, if I got the same rate I should have had far more when I was getting older - getting in my teens.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 You mentioned threepence in the shilling at one stage didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 That's right - that's when I was getting in me teens.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 After your penny in the shilling you went up you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh yes, yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 In your half time job how did you get on with the other people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 All right apparently. I never had any arguments.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Were they all much older than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh yes, yes, I was the junior, very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 How did your employer treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Do you mean my particular boss or the manager or -?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Well both.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Well, my particular boss wasn't so bad but - to manager I was less than the dirt under his feet. I was like a little insect. 'Course he wasn't the best of men.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Was his attitude the same towards the other workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes. Oh yes, it wasn't just me particularly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 How did you feel about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Well I wasn't pleased. But there was nothing I could do about it. I just had to accept it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 How did you feel about the work? Did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Well it was too - monotonous shall I say. Too much repetition.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 After you'd done this as a half timer I take it that you carried on doing it as a full timer initially did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh yes, that's right, yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 You were in the same environment and working under the same conditions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 That's right - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 And for the same amount of money relatively?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 That's right - yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 How long would you stay in that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Perhaps about twelve months I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Full time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Certainly - yes - certainly not more than two years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 That would take us up to about 1913?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Where are we - about sixteen or fifteen. Fifteen or sixteen wouldn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 1913 would be when you would start?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 That's right - I was twelve in 1913. And then I were full time in
 '14 so it would be roughly '16. '15 or '16. I couldn't just say now off hand just how long it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did you just have one other job then before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes, only one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 How long did you stay in that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh - good number of years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Can you tell me something about that one - you transferred to spinning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 That's right - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 What exactly was your job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Little piece - what they call little piecerman. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 How did you get that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Well, there was the - boys round
 about home - that friendly with and - oh they had a grand time in the mill and they wanted-labour so I just - went and was accepted and carry on. Oh I had to see - had to pass a medical examination. And - O.K. - they wanted the labour and that was it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Would the mill hours there be the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Just the same. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 The wage was a bit better?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Rather more - yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Nine shillings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did that increase at all while you were a little piecer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 I'm just wonderin
g when the increases came now. It may have increased alightly by virtue of the whole trade getting a rise. The union effort sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did you go on giving the money intact to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh yes. Yes, yes. All the time I was at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 First you got a penny in the shilling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 That's right - and then threepence - that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did you get the threepence in the shilling when you started getting the nine shilling?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Now then - it may have been when I got the nine shillings. Yes
. That's right. You see, it's so difficult to remember just when these things did happen actually. Yes, I think it was. Yes, and then of course as I got older it gradually increased - gradually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 How did you get on with the people there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 All right - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Were you happier?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Much happier. Oh yes. Although later on as I got - promotion - got side piecing - the monotony of the job struck me then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 How long was it before you went onto side piecing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Now then - about two or three years I think. I couldn't say off hand how.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 But it would be in the same mill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 What was the employer like there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 My immediate boss wasn't so bad and there again - the overlooker or foremen - was very short tempered, he wasn't 
popular at all. I didn't have much to do with him but - he was no friend of mine. Don't know why he should be - should have been like that. But I've met him several times since and he wanted to be most friendly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 How did you feel about your work as a little piecer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Oh it was grand for beginning. But somehow I had an idea at the back of my mind I was fit for better things. But the opportunity didn't come.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 So you went onto side piecing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 That would take you up to the end of the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh beyond that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 What jobs have you done since then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Well, I got sick of it - then I went into partnership with my brother and we opened the fish and chip business.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Around about when would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Be getting
 towards 1930 I think. Yes, I think it was. And we were there and then - my brother left the business and I carried on for some time but my wife didn't like the business so - I finally sold it and that would be 1936 I think it was. Yes, I think it was 193
6. And then - then I was offered a job - like being in cotton waste firm. So rather than be out of work or that I took it. And I stayed with that firm since. Up to retiring. But I wasn't labouring when I finished. It was a good move.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 What work did you go on to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
I became the foreman warehouseman in the cotton waste. But we didn't process it at all. We simply bought it in bag and resold it partly in bag and partly in bale. We pressed part of it into bales - sold it by bale and others were sold just 
in bags it come from the mill. The only difference was that - the mills took the longer fibres. And of course the shorter fibres dropped through so of course we bought them and resold them and they were all processed. Nothing wasted.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 You say you felt you could have done better things if the opportunity had arisen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Was there any particular occupation that you feel you would have preferred?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 What I would liked to have done - then, was to go to school and university and entered the c
hurch. But it wasn't possible - for - home circumstances for one reason because being a big family my money was necessary. And - well I couldn't let them - withdrawn because I should have wanted keeping while I was training. And as I say, the family neede
d money - so I was anchored.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did you serve an apprenticeship or training period for any of your jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did you belong to any trade union or organisation of any kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Only - well - yes, I had to - pay to the spinners union I thin
k. It wasn't much but it was paid through my immediate employer - through the spinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 That was the custom wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 That's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 What about when you were in the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh, I beg your pardon. Yes. When we were in the fish and chip business we joined the - eeh what's the actual definition?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 The Trade Association?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes. The National Association of Fish Fryers. Or something of the sort.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did you take part in any of the union activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 No. Oh, hold on a minute - 
oh still that - that won't matter will it - because during the - the last war I was moved from my own job up to Carlisle on more important war work and I was moved up to R.A.F. Maintainance Unit. And I was up there five months and then I heard they were t
r
ansferring office to Bolton so I applied for a transfer with it. And I got it. And - we had to - well, not that we had to - join the Civil Service Union. And they made me their representative. But that won't apply to this will it. Too late. That's the onl
y other union I've been - member of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 You didn't take an active part in anything the spinners were doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh dear me no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did you feel that employers and workers had the same interests in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 No. No, different interests. My i
mpression was that the employers wanted - the work and the money - money - and of course the working - the operatives were just there for the money. Of course they needed the money to live but apart from that - I don't think they'd much interest in the jo
b - generally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did you feel that there were divisions of interest amongst workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Only that each wanted almost - as much money as he could get. And of course the usual ones - if they can steal a march on their follow man they will.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did you feel that there was a great division between the trained craftsman and the other workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Well - of course there is a division - definite division. But I wouldn't say there is a great division. Because - and yet on the other hand it is a great divisi
on because in the spinning at all events the labourers cannot become spinners. Partly through the trade union and partly through the fact - they haven't the skill. Nor would they be allowed to acquire it. Because there was the usual ladder - they started 
l
ittle piecer, side piecer and then spinner. But of course since I was there I believe that's changed now. I don't know quite what the definitions are now. I think the side piecers gone. And it's assistant minder or something or assistant spinner. No, I do
n't know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Would you say that your work changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Yes, I think it did a little. The world seemed an entirely different place once I started working. And I also I began to realise that the freedom that I tho
ught I should have when I began to work was non-existent. There was just as much discipline in another direction when I was working as there was in school. In essnece it was a case of changing one master for another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 You continued to live at home after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Would you say that starting full time work changed your relationship with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Or with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 No. Except that I thought I was a bigger person - to my brothers and sisters. I was someone of consequence now I was employed full time.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did you spend your Sunday any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did you begin to take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 No. Rightly or wrongly I'm afraid they never interested me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Have you exercised your vote at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh yes, yes, I think - I think that's a duty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 What party have you voted for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Conservative.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Always?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 I think so. Partly on account of the policy and partly on account of the man. I don't
 feel hidebound to any particular party. Because I think - they can all stretch the truth and of course they all put the best case for themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 You wouldn't be old enough to vote at an election before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 If you weren't interested you wouldn't be holding any office within the party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh no, I wasn't. No. Oh Lord no, I've never had any office in any particular political party - sorry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 You've already mentioned how you spent your spare time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Music, choral music. Photography.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 You continued some of the things you did at while at school and you added some things didn't you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did you go out in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh yes, quite a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Apart from in connection with the specific activities you've already mentioned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Not often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Were there any places you would go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
I liked to go to a theatre. Or a good musical concert. I didn't often go to the cinema because it - well, I say, it always left me dissatisfied, it still does
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Who would you go with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Usually friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did you make any new friends when you started to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
I don't think I made any close friends. Because when - no - because there were no other boys where I started work. And I went in the spinning mill - I alre
ady knew the boys round about sort of thing. I was friendly with them then so - I didn't need anyone else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did you make any girlfriends about then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 No. Not -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did you bring your friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 You'd been in the habit of doing that before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 That's right - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 So your parents would meet your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 True. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did your parents expect to know where you were when you were out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 No, no. So long as - we were in at a reasonable time that's all that mattered.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Did they specify a time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 
Invariably - I can't just think now just what time it was originally. 'Course for a youngster about that - about ten or eleven - 1911 it wouldn't be much beyond eight o'clock - if it was beyond eight o'clock I 
don't think it was. Then as we got a little older it went a little later.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 When you were owning your own living when you were about eighteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh, half past ten or eleven o'clock. There was no - no hard and fast line but of course we had to use reason.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 You were allowed a little latitude?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636965 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 I think that's all I have to ask you unless you have anything of interest you would like to add?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11944731 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14686165\charrsid13851071 Within that period? I'm afraid I can't think of anything offhand.
